A Nashville bar owner was convicted of second-degree murder on Friday for the fatal shooting of a country singer-songwriter.

Chris Ferrell, 46, had told jurors that he shot Wayne Mills in November 2013 in self defense. But Nashville jurors sided with prosecutors who argued that Ferrell intended to kill Mills when he shot him after a heated argument at his now-defunct bar.

Ferrell testified that the two got into an argument at his Pit and Barrel bar in the city's downtown area and that Mills threatened to kill him.

